A Census of Edge-Transitive Tetravalent Graphs
fields.complete: There are three kinds of edge-transitive tetravalent graphs, namely: dart-transitive, half-arc-transitive and semisymmetric. This Census inherits completeness in the first two categories from studies by Potočnik, Spiga and Verret. The third category is not known to be complete and we strongly suspect that it is not.
fields.summaryOfFAIR: The paper (part of the metadata) is not yet published (January 2019).  Every graph has a unique identifier (C4[n, i]), an encyclopedic page (the URL is deducible from its identifier).  The dataset is available as a Magma file and the properties as an Excel file.

fields.name: Calabi-Yau data
fields.description: Numerical data of Calabi-Yau manifolds of various dimensions (K3 spaces, Calabi-Yau threefolds, higher dimensional CY manifolds)
fields.comment: [theoretical physics] The data also contain information on the authors' classification scheme for reflexive polyhedra and data of Landau-Ginzburg models and reflexive Gorenstein cones.
fields.summaryOfFAIR: The authors provide a program for creating and manipulating the data.

fields.name: Graded Ring Database
fields.description: A database of graded rings in algebraic geometry, including classifications of toric varieties, polarised K3 surfaces, and Fano 3-folds and 4-folds.
fields.comment:
Each database search page includes details of the authors of that data, together with papers that should be cited when you use the data. Please also reference the Graded Ring Database.
Several of the calculations are performed using the Magma computational algebra system. Other software used in construction of the data include PALP, polymake, and LattE.

fields.name: Table of AME states
fields.description: able on the existence of absolutely maximally entangled states (AME) of n parties with D levels each.
fields.comment:
The database list a type of quantum codes that could be considered to
be self-dual. More precisely, the table lists pure ((n,1,n/2+1))_D
quantum error correcting codes, both of stabilizer and non-stabilizer
type.
